*{{note label|Note04|d|d}}Pick was a lottery bonus pick.<ref name="profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1947">{{cite web|url=http://www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1947.jsp|title=Pro Football Draft History: 1947|accessdate=2009-05-03}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note05|e|e}}Pick acquired from Detroit through Pittsburgh.<ref name="profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1948">{{cite web|url=http://www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1948.jsp|title=Pro Football Draft History: 1948|accessdate=2009-05-01}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note06|f|f}} Acquired from New York Bulldogs.<ref name="profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1950">{{cite web|url=http://www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1950.jsp|title=Pro Football Draft History: 1950|accessdate=2009-05-01}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note07|g|g}} Acquired from the Baltimore Colts.<ref name="profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1951">{{cite web|url=http://www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1951.jsp|title=Pro Football Draft History: 1951|accessdate=2009-05-01}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note08|h|h}}Acquired from the Baltimore Colts.<ref name="profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1951">{{cite web|url=http://www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1951.jsp|title=Pro Football Draft History: 1951|accessdate=2009-05-01}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note09|i|i}}Pick acquired from Pittsburgh Steelers.<ref name="www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1963">{{cite web|url=http://www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1963.jsp|title=Pro Football Draft History: 1963|accessdate=2009-07-08}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note10|j|j}}Pick acquired from Pittsburgh Steelers.<ref name="www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1965">{{cite web|url=http://www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1965.jsp|title=Pro Football Draft History: 1965|accessdate=2009-07-08}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note11|k|k}}Pick acquired from Washington Redskins.<ref name="www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1965">{{cite web|url=http://www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1965.jsp|title=Pro Football Draft History: 1965|accessdate=2009-07-08}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note12|l|l}}Second overall selection traded to Green Bay Packers (who selected [[Mike McCoy]]) for [[Bob Hyland]], [[Elijah Pitts]], [[Lee Roy Caffey]].<ref name="www.packers.com/history/record_book/results_and_rosters/significant_trades/">{{cite web|url=http://www.packers.com/history/record_book/results_and_rosters/significant_trades/|title=Packers Significant Trades, 1957-2008|date=1-29-09|publisher=Packers.com|accessdate=2009-07-08}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note13|m|m}}Pick acquired from New York Giants.<ref name="www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1972">{{cite web|url=http://www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1972.jsp|title=Pro Football Draft History: 1972|accessdate=2009-07-08}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note14|n|n}}Acquired from Washington Redskins through Los Angeles Rams.<ref name="www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1974">{{cite web|url=http://www.profootballhof.com/history/general/draft/1974.jsp|title=Pro Football Draft History: 1974|accessdate=2009-07-08}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note15|o|o}} Pick acquired from Green Bay through Los Angeles Rams and Detroit Lions. Bears, in exchange, sent 1976 10th overall pick ([[James Hunter]]) and 68th overall pick ([[Russ Bolinger]]) to Lions.
*{{note label|Note16|p|p}} Bears traded 1978 20th overall pick (eventually [[Elvis Peacock]]) to Cleveland Browns for [[Mike Phipps]].
*{{note label|Note17|q|q}} Bears traded Wally Chambers to Tampa Bay Buccaneers for this pick and Bobby Moore (player named later).<ref name="St. Petersburg Times">{{cite news|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=TBgMAAAAIBAJ&sjid=GVoDAAAAIBAJ&pg=6105,6189086|title=Bay Bucs sign Chambers but give up Moore|last=Martz|first=Ron |date=4-15-1978|publisher=St. Petersburg Times|pages=99 of 127|language=English|accessdate=2009-07-08}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note18|r|r}}Pick acquired from Tampa Bay Buccaneers. Bears traded 1982 second round selection (32nd overall [[Booker Reese]]) to Tampa Bay for a 1983 first round selection (18th overall Willie Gault).<ref name="sportsillustrated.cnn.com/football/nfl/news/2001/02/12/sayitaintso_buccaneers/">{{cite web|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/football/nfl/news/2001/02/12/sayitaintso_buccaneers/|title=Say It Ain't So: Tampa Bay Buccaneers|date=2001|publisher=CNNSI.com|accessdate=2009-07-09}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note19|s|s}} Bears acquired 1988 27th overall pick (Wendell Davis) and 1989's 12th selection (Trace Armstrong) from the Washington Redskins as compensation for Washington signing free agent Wilbur Marshall.<ref name="vault.sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1127112/index.htm">{{cite web|url=http://vault.sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1127112/index.htm|title=Getting Free For A Big Gain|last=Zimmerman|first=Paul|date=3-28-88|publisher=sportsillustrated.com|accessdate=2009-07-09}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note20|t|t}} Bears traded 1997 first round selection (11th overall) to the [[Seattle Seahawks]] for [[Rick Mirer]].<ref name="sportsillustrated.cnn.com/football/nfl/news/2001/03/29/sayitaintso_bears/">{{cite web|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/football/nfl/news/2001/03/29/sayitaintso_bears/|title=Say It Ain't So: Chicago Bears|date=2001|publisher=CNNSI.com|accessdate=2009-07-09}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note21|u|u}} Bears traded 1999 first round pick (7th overall) to the Washington Redskins for their 1999 first round pick (12th overall), 1999 third round pick (71 overall), 1999 fourth round pick (106 overall), 1999 fifth round pick (144 overall), and 2000 third round pick (87 overall).
*{{note label|Note22|v|v}} Bears traded their 2003 first round selection (4 overall) to the [[New York Jets]] for 2 2003 first round selections (13 and 22 overall) and 2003 fourth round pick (116 overall).<ref name="www.usatoday.com/sports/football/draft/2003-04-25-jets-bears-trade_x.htm">{{cite web|url=http://www.usatoday.com/sports/football/draft/2003-04-25-jets-bears-trade_x.htm|title=Jets trade two picks to Bears for fourth overall|date=4-25-03|publisher=AP|accessdate=2009-07-10}}</ref> The Bears then traded 2003 13th overall pick to the New England Patriots for 2003 14th overall pick and a 2003 sixth round pick (193 overall).
*{{note label|Note23|w|w}} Bears traded 2006 first round pick (26 overall) to Buffalo Bills for 2006 second round pick (42 overall), and 2006 third round pick (73 overall).<ref name="www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-145239013.html">{{cite web|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-145239013.html|title=Safety 1st for Bears Trade down to get Manning with draft's 42nd overall pick|last=LeGere|first=Bob|date=4-30-06|publisher=Daily Herald|accessdate=2009-07-10}}</ref>
*{{note label|Note24|x|x}} Bears traded [[Kyle Orton]], first found picks in 2009 (18th overall) and 2010, and 2009 3rd round pick (84 overall) to the Denver Broncos for [[Jay Cutler (American football)|Jay Cutler]].<ref name="sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=4037373">{{cite web|url=http://sports.espn.go.com/nfl/news/story?id=4037373|title=Cutler goes to Bears for Orton, picks|date=4-03-09|publisher=ESPN.com|accessdate=2009-07-09}}</ref>
